<font color="#FF0000">TO SPATZ</font><br>
<tt>Sun Nov 23  2:24:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
First off spatz. I have no Post Tramatic Stress Disorder. I don't hide behind anything. Never have.<br><br>
Let me point out how you hide. You posted a denigrating post about Art Varanelli a couple of weeks ago. I have to admit that it was mild compared to the type of stuff you are posting nowadays. Still, I posted a message where I thought that you should apologize. You must have taken it to heart because, soon, you came out with the juvenile excuse that someone else posted the message! I don't think you have a pair of stones, spatz. The vile messages you post now are positive proof that it was you who posted all the messages you have denied.<br><br>
Next, I come home tonite and read your assault on Edward's daughter. Call us baby killers, nazi's and murderers. But, leave children out of it. <br><br>
As for Cook being anti semitic, I think that he is quite capable of defending himself. I don't think that he is anti anything. What you fail to understand is that many men who served in Vietnam simply don't like those who protested. I don't agree, but I understand why Cook feels the way he feels about protestors. <br><br>
I think that CO's are and were very misunderstood. For instance, the other CO I knew who served in Vietnam was named Frank Garcia. He lived around San Francisco. Many times he risked his life aiding his fellow soldiers. Yes, he was a soldier, but he was one who didn't carry a weapon. He caught an AK round on Highway 5b near the Tra Khuc River, and was dusted off. When the Medivac was taking off he was wounded a second time.<br><br>
I remember a couple of days later how our Commanding Officer was discussing our getting another medic. He was vehemently opposed to having another CO. It wasn't that he didn't like Rocky (his nick), he plainly stated that he needed another rifle in the field. It was war, spatz. You have never seen or experienced anything like it. For some reason that little voice in your ear keeps prodding you to continue your attempt to put yourself on an equal footing with men like Frank Garcia and Art Combs. You are wasting your time. Yes these men were Co's, but they will always be heroes in my heart. They understood the nature of war and would not have called us babykillers or murderers as you do. You simply don't understand.<br><br>
As for my providing information to students: I am very comfortable about who I am and am consistent in the information I provide. As I stated earlier I give out the good and the bad. I distinctly recall inviting you to write about your experiences, but you never took me up on my offer. So, don't try to make it as if I am hiding behind anything. <br><br>
I would guess that you weren't much of a poker player. You are no match for anyone here. You are a very transparent person.<br>

<p><code>-- wingman%greene.xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


